What is Off-Price Retail?
Off-price retail operates on a fundamentally different model than traditional retail channels. Instead of following seasonal merchandising calendars, off-price retailers purchase excess, over-produced, or out-of-season branded goods at significant discounts. These savings are then passed along to consumers through typically 20-60% discounts off regular retail prices. The sector thrives on opportunistic buying, with retailers maintaining flexible supply chains to capitalize on inventory surpluses from manufacturers and department stores.
