Regional Market Insights
•	North America: The most mature off-price market, led by the U.S. where consumers have fully embraced the value proposition. Market saturation in major metro areas is driving expansion into secondary cities.
•	Europe: Growing steadily, particularly in the UK and Germany. The market benefits from tourist shopping and increasing outlet mall development.
•	Asia-Pacific: Shows the highest growth potential long-term, though cultural preferences for new merchandise and less liquid inventory markets present unique challenges.
•	Latin America: Early stage development focused primarily on Brazil and Mexico, with growth tied to economic stabilization and retail modernization.
