 Competitive Landscape
The market features a mix of large national chains and regional specialists, with the top four players controlling about 21% of the global market. TJX Companies (TJ Maxx, Marshalls) remains the clear leader through its extensive store network and sophisticated supply chain capabilities. Ross Stores follows with its disciplined approach to inventory management and pricing. Other notable competitors include Burlington Stores, Nordstrom Rack, and various regional players adapting the model to local market conditions.
Recent competitive developments include:
•	Expansion of private label and exclusive brand offerings to differentiate assortments
•	Testing of smaller format stores for urban markets
•	Investments in data analytics to optimize merchandise allocation and pricing
